  "response": "No, pigeons do not settle on windows to reflect on existence. Pigeons are generally attracted to windowsills and ledges for more practical reasons. They might be looking for a place to rest, a vantage point to survey their surroundings, or a spot to potentially find food. If you have a photo of a pigeon on a windowsill, it's likely there for one of these reasons rather than philosophical contemplation!",
